    "content": "The <strong>national symbols</strong> of Scotland include the <strong>Saltire</strong> (the white cross of Saint Andrew on a blue background), the <strong>thistle</strong> (a purple-flowered plant), and the <strong>unicorn</strong>, which is the country’s official <strong>national animal</strong>. The unicorn represents <strong>purity</strong>, <strong>innocence</strong>, and <strong>power</strong>.</p><p>",
