    "content": "Scotland has a rich <strong>culinary tradition</strong>, featuring iconic foods such as <strong>haggis</strong> (a savory pudding made from sheep’s offal), <strong>shortbread</strong> (a sweet buttery biscuit), and <strong>tablet</strong> (a crumbly fudge). Scotland is also famous for producing <strong>Scotch whisky</strong>, which is made in regions like <strong>Speyside</strong>, <strong>Islay</strong>, and the <strong>Highlands</strong>.</p><p>",
